&lt;p&gt;· Develop clear project scopes and analyze project requirements to identify potential risks and cost-saving opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Prepare comprehensive proposals, including detailed cost breakdowns, project timelines, and scope of work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Review architectural, structural, and civil plans and specifications to identify design related issues and potential risks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Develop and maintain strong relationships with subcontractors and vendors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Negotiate contracts with clients, ensuring profitability and adherence to project specifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with project managers to ensure smooth execution and timely completion of projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Adhere to all safety regulations and guidelines to maintain a safe work environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Keep abreast of industry trends, new technologies, and regulatory changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Bachelor’s degree in construction management, Civil Engineering or related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· 10+ years of Civil, Structural and Architectural estimating&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Proficiency in estimating software, CAD software, and Microsoft Office Suite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Strong understanding of construction methods, materials and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
